						<!-- firstHeading -->
			<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en"><span dir="auto">Resignation of Pope Benedict XVI</span></h1>
			<!-- /firstHeading -->
			<!-- bodyContent -->
			<div id="bodyContent">
								<!-- tagline -->
				<div id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
				<!-- /tagline -->
								<!-- subtitle -->
				<div id="contentSub"></div>
				<!-- /subtitle -->
																<!-- jumpto -->
				<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">
					Jump to:					<a href="#mw-head">navigation</a>, 					<a href="#p-search">search</a>
				</div>
				<!-- /jumpto -->
								<!-- bodycontent -->
				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:BentoXVI-29-10052007.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fe/BentoXVI-29-10052007.jpg/220px-BentoXVI-29-10052007.jpg" width="220" height="536" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fe/BentoXVI-29-10052007.jpg/330px-BentoXVI-29-10052007.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fe/BentoXVI-29-10052007.jpg/440px-BentoXVI-29-10052007.jpg 2x" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:BentoXVI-29-10052007.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="http://bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf9/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
Pope Benedict XVI in 2007.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>The pending <b>resignation of Pope Benedict XVI</b> was announced on the morning of 11 February 2013, when the <a href="Holy_See" title="Holy See">Vatican</a> confirmed that <a href="Pope_Benedict_XVI" title="Pope Benedict XVI">Pope Benedict XVI</a> would <a href="Papal_resignation" title="Papal resignation">resign the papacy</a> on 28 February.<sup id="cite_ref-Guardian-2013-02-11_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Guardian-2013-02-11-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> Benedict's decision to step down as leader of the <a href="Roman_Catholic_Church" title="Roman Catholic Church" class="mw-redirect">Roman Catholic Church</a> will make him the first pope to relinquish the office since <a href="Pope_Gregory_XII" title="Pope Gregory XII">Pope Gregory XII</a> in 1415<sup id="cite_ref-resignCNN_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-resignCNN-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup> (who did so in order to end the <a href="Western_Schism" title="Western Schism">Western Schism</a>), and the first to do so of his own free will since <a href="Pope_Celestine_V" title="Pope Celestine V">Pope Celestine V</a> in 1294.<sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup> The move was unexpected,<sup id="cite_ref-BBCresign1_4-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-BBCresign1-4"><span>[</span>4<span>]</span></a></sup> as in the <a href="Modern_history" title="Modern history">modern era</a> popes have held the position from election until death.<sup id="cite_ref-BBCresign1_4-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-BBCresign1-4"><span>[</span>4<span>]</span></a></sup> As early as 2010, several secular and liberal Catholics were calling for Pope Benedict XVI's resignation, citing the actions of then Cardinal Ratzinger's blocking of efforts to remove a <a href="Catholic_sex_abuse_cases" title="Catholic sex abuse cases">priest convicted</a> of child abuse.<sup id="cite_ref-nty_5-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-nty-5"><span>[</span>5<span>]</span></a></sup> The Pope stated that the reason for his decision was his declining health.</p>
